title: Prep Spotlight: Williamsville wins outright Sangamo volleyball title
text: Posted Oct. 22, 2015 at 10:12 PM Posted Oct. 22, 2015 at 10:12 PM MASON CITY — Williamsville defeated Mason City Illini Central 25-12, 25-10 Thursday and won the outright Sangamo Conference volleyball title with a 9-0 record. Delaney Edwards compiled 15 kills and Abbey Galusha added eight kills for Williamsville. Leah Musselman totaled 31 assists and Maggie Sorenson collected 21 digs as the Bullets improved to 26-4 overall. Ally Karras and Edwards led Williamsville with two service aces each. Carlee Bale finished with four kills and Gabby Williams had 10 assists for Illini Central (8-17). SHG rallies past Green Wave MATTOON — Emma Hopkins had 12 kills and 11 digs as Sacred Heart-Griffin got past Mattoon, 22-25, 25-21, 25-21 in the Cyclones’ regular-season finale. The victory by SHG (25-8) avenged a recent three-set loss to Mattoon (24-11) in a tournament and sends the newly minted Central State Eight champ into next week’s Class 3A regional with some momentum. Annie Urbance and Eilise Cummins had 12 and nine kills, respectively, for SHG, which also got 11 digs from Makayla Yoho and 20 assists from Alli Lanzotti. Elle Drake and Emily Watson had nine kills apiece for the Green Wave. Heyen powers Greenview MORRISONVILLE — Evelyn Heyen collected 16 kills and 15 blocks in Greenview’s 23-25, 25-18, 25-21 win over Morrisonville. Kirsten March had 21 assists. Destiny VanCleve recorded 20 digs for Greenview (10-20). Beckers, Davis lead Hilltoppers AUBURN — Alexandra Beckers had 21 assists and Maddy Davis had nine kills for Mount Pulaski in a 25-15, 25-20 victory over Auburn. Abigail Fitzgerald finished with 10 digs. Pawnee tops Riverton PAWNEE — Kiley Craigmiles and Chelby Harden had nine kills apiece in Pawnee’s 25-16, 25-22 win over Riverton in a Sangamo Conference match. Morgan Worker had 10 assists for Pawnee. Mackenzy Payne had eight assists for Riverton. Teammate Abby Walters added 12 digs. Bruntjen, Krager lead 27-2 Lancers RAYMOND — Karly Bruntjen slammed 10 kills and Skylar Krager provided 25 assists to lead Raymond Lincolnwood past Staunton 25-5, 25-13. Lincolnwood improved to 27-2. Haidyn Glick added seven kills and two blocks and Rachael Gorman served 17 points and got 13 digs for the Lancers. Sarah Williams led Staunton (9-18) with two kills. Tapscott delivers for Athens ATHENS — Micah Tapscott produced 17 kills to help Athens defeat North Mac 22-25, 25-15, 25-22. McKenzie Wasilewski finished with 19 assists and Lauren Ethell was solid defensively, getting 24 digs for Athens. Wasilewski collected 15 digs and Demi Cushman and Tapscott both had three blocks. Brenda Barnes led North Mac with 11 kills, while Hannah Tomasko served eight aces and chipped in 16 digs. Lauren Mulacek had 22 assists for North Mac. Lutheran sweeps Edinburg Page 2 of 2 - Dominant performances by Seton Tournoux and Kiersten Anderson helped host Lutheran beat Edinburg 25-12, 25-4. Tournoux had 12 digs and an incredible 24 service points, including four aces, most of that coming in the 25-4 second set. Meanwhile, Kiersten Anderson spiked down 17 kills (with 3 blocks) while younger sister Cara Anderson racked up 15 assists. Edinburg’s Karlee Herzog and Sam Sabo had 12 and nine digs, respectively. Havana downs Triopia in two HAVANA — Caity Specketer had five kills and Haley Gilmore added 15 assists as Havana defeated Concord Triopia 25-23, 25-21. Sadie Dodds and Echo Pringle had four kills each for the Ducks. Pringle also had two blocks. Havana won the JV match, 19-25, 26-24, 16-14. Pana goes 9-0 in South Central PANA — The Pana Panthers wrapped up the South Central Conference title Thursday with a 25-17, 25-19 victory over Vandalia. The Panthers (23-12, 9-0 South Central) rode the hot hand of Lexie Siegert (seven kills, six blocks) and Shayna Stremming (six kills, four digs) to the two-set victory. Laurel Funneman had 10 assists for Pana. PORTA takes down South County PETERSBURG — Martina Galiotto had 12 kills, Sidney Donnan had 19 assists and Kaycee Turasky got down for 21 digs to lead Petersburg PORTA to a 25-11, 25-19 victory over the Vipers. Briley Eilers had four ace serves for the Blue Jays (16-12) and Brittany Smith added six kills and eight digs. South County (14-16) got nine digs and two ace serves from Kaylee Grider. IN OTHER NEWS: AUBREY HUNT recorded 10 kills, four digs and two blocks to carry host Niantic Sangamon Valley past Argenta-Oreana 27-25, 25-13. BRITTANY MCCLELLAND served three aces and TAYLOR CAMPBELL racked up 18 assists for Sangamon Valley. SWIMMING Cyclones rout PORTA Abby Fierstos, Cami Blair and Megan Rupnik all won two individual events as Sacred Heart-Griffin beat Petersburg PORTA 140-26 in a dual meet at Eisenhower Pool. Fierstos won the 200-yard individual medley in 2 minutes 27.60 seconds and took the 100-yard butterfly in 1:05.09. Rupnik captured first in the 100 freestyle in 1:03.59 while winning the 100 backstroke in 1:13.15. Blair was first in both the 100 backstroke in 1:19.66 and the 500 freestyle in 5:43.84. The State Journal-Register
